  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Reproduced on 1.11.7 as well as master-ish (a92729a301c8928d8e108418e6e4625a9e0d6733)\r\n\r\nDeleting a CRD doesn't seem to cause the API server to terminate watches referencing the corresponding CRs, but the watches also don't properly resume if the CRD is created again, meaning that you have to wait for watch timeouts to actually get new watch events.\r\n\r\nWe should probably kill open watches on CRD deletion, so that clients are notified and are forced to re-watch.  Either that, or seamlessly resume watches if a CRD is recreated.\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproducer:\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>crd.yaml</summary>\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1beta1\r\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: testcrds.metamagical.io\r\nspec:\r\n  group: metamagical.io\r\n  version: v1\r\n  names:\r\n    kind: TestCRD\r\n    plural: testcrds\r\n  scope: Namespaced\r\n  validation:\r\n    openAPIV3Schema:\r\n      properties:\r\n        apiVersion:\r\n          type: string\r\n        kind:\r\n          type: string\r\n        metadata:\r\n          type: object\r\n        spec:\r\n          type: object\r\n          properties:\r\n            count: {type: integer}\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>cr.yaml</summary>\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: metamagical.io/v1\r\nkind: TestCRD\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: testcr\r\nspec:\r\n  count: 3\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n1. Create the above CRD: `kubectl create -f crd.yaml`\r\n2. Create the above CR: `kubectl create -f cr.yaml`\r\n3. (elsewhere) `kubectl proxy`\r\n4. `curl localhost:8001/apis/metamagical.io/v1/testcrds` and grab a resource version\r\n5. (elsewhere) `curl localhost:8001/apis/metamagical.io/v1/testcrds?watch=1&resourceVersion=<above>`\r\n6. `kubectl delete -f cr.yaml`\r\n7. `kubectl delete -f crd.yaml`\r\n8. `kubectl create -f crd.yaml`\r\n9. `kubectl create -f cr.yaml`\r\n10. Observe the lack of watch events\r\n\r\nAfter watches time out, things can re-establish, but that can be a while.",
